# Frontend Tests Required

Every new or meaningfully changed frontend **page** or **component** must ship with tests and those tests must pass before considering the work done.

## Stack

- **Runner**: Vitest (`npm test` / `npm run test:watch` from `frontend/`)
- **Library**: React Testing Library + `@testing-library/jest-dom`
- **Location**: Colocate as `ComponentName.test.tsx` next to the source file
- **Shared fixtures**: Reuse or extend `src/test/fixtures.ts`; mock API modules with `vi.mock('../api')` (or `./api`)

## Requirements

- Add or update tests in the same change set as the page/component.
- Cover the main user-visible paths: loading, error (+ retry when present), and happy path. Add empty-state coverage when the UI has one.
- Pages that fetch data must mock `../api` — do not hit the network.
- Run the suite and fix failures before finishing:

```bash
# From frontend/
npm test
```

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: new page with no tests
// frontend/src/pages/Standings.tsx
// (no Standings.test.tsx)

// ✅ GOOD: colocated tests that pass
// frontend/src/pages/Standings.tsx
// frontend/src/pages/Standings.test.tsx  // loading, error+retry, happy path
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: change UI contract, leave assertions stale or skip failing tests
// ✅ GOOD: update assertions, keep suite green, no .skip to hide gaps
```

## Checklist before done

- [ ] Colocated `*.test.tsx` exists for the new/changed page or component
- [ ] Loading / error / happy paths covered where applicable
- [ ] `npm test` passes
- [ ] No skipped tests used to hide broken coverage
